========================================================
OBJECTIVE
========================================================

Perform a complete repository-wide security-focused API and servlet endpoint discovery.

The task is to:

- Scan EVERY file in the repository recursively.
- Determine whether the file contains:
  - API endpoints
  - REST endpoints
  - GraphQL endpoints
  - SOAP endpoints
  - Servlet mappings
  - Web service routes
  - Controller mappings
  - Internal endpoints
  - Gateway/proxy routes
  - Request handlers

Extract:

- Endpoint path
- HTTP method
- Parameters
- Parameter types
- Authentication requirements
- Request body usage
- Response/output details
- File path
- Class name
- Method name
- Framework used
- Security observations
- Invocation flow (if traceable)

Nothing should be skipped.

Every file must be reviewed to determine whether APIs/endpoints are present.

Even if a file contains no API definitions, it must still be evaluated and documented.

========================================================
MANDATORY SCAN REQUIREMENTS
========================================================

Recursively scan all directories and file types, including but not limited to:

- .java
- .kt
- .groovy
- .scala
- .xml
- .properties
- .yml
- .yaml
- .json
- .js
- .ts
- .py
- .cs
- .go
- .php
- .rb
- .jsp
- .jspx
- .html
- .sql
- build scripts
- deployment descriptors
- configuration files

Do NOT ignore:

- legacy modules
- generated folders
- archived modules
- hidden folders
- nested repositories
- shared libraries
- internal frameworks

