========================================================
SECURITY ANALYSIS REQUIREMENTS
========================================================

For every endpoint discovered, identify and document:

- Authentication mechanism
- Authorization checks
- Role-based restrictions
- Token usage
- JWT handling
- Session handling
- API keys
- OAuth/OpenID references
- Input validation presence
- SQL injection risk indicators
- File upload handling
- Deserialization risks
- Sensitive data exposure
- Debug/test endpoints
- Hardcoded secrets
- Unsafe HTTP methods
- CORS configuration
- Exception leakage
- Logging of sensitive data

If observable, include:
- downstream service calls
- database interactions
- external integrations
- request forwarding
- redirect behavior

========================================================
PARAMETER EXTRACTION REQUIREMENTS
========================================================

Extract all identifiable parameters:

- query parameters
- path variables
- request body fields
- headers
- cookies
- multipart parameters
- form fields
- matrix params

For each parameter include:

- parameter name
- parameter type
- required/optional
- default value if available
- source location

